podcast_description: Your weekly rhetorical assault on the on the news cycle, the people who make it, and occasionally ourselves. Kmele Foster (Freethink), Michael Moynihan (Vice), and Matt Welch (Reason) talk and laugh and drink their way to at least quasi-sanity in a world gone mad, often with the aid of clean and articulate guests. Weekly Members Only subscription edition often comes with listener mail and professional-quality (if inappropriate) singing. Analysis. Commentary. Sedition.

viralGiftsConfig.grant_email_body: {"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"哈囉！我是區塊勢的作者許明恩。"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"感謝你成為區塊勢的訂閱會員。正是因為有你的付費支持，區塊勢這家獨立媒體才能持續成長，並為中文領域貢獻更多原創 Web3 內容。而不只是一昧的翻譯國外文章。"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"如果你曾經想要推薦身邊的親朋好友閱讀區塊勢，但對方卻因為付費門檻而猶豫不決，現在你可以大方地跟他說：「不妨把 email 告訴我，我送你一個月訂閱會員試試看？」"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"這是區塊勢近期新推出的【會員推薦計畫】。現在你可以點擊下方按鈕，並推薦 3 位朋友訂閱區塊勢。每位被你推薦的朋友，都可以獲得區塊勢會員資格一個月。等於是你自掏腰包，送他們訂閱區塊勢。"}]},{"type":"button","attrs":{"url":"%%grant_gift_url%%","text":"Give a subscription","action":null,"class":"left"}},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"理論上每位會員每隔半年就會獲得 3 個推薦名額，數量應該是相當夠用。不必節省。如果日後有人問你區塊勢的內容如何，除了可以請他參考"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://blocktrend.substack.com/about","target":"_blank"}}],"text":"讀者證詞"},{"type":"text","text":"、"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://www.notion.so/blocktrend/803ea6a37d444e67b403e515572ace58","target":"_blank"}}],"text":"文章列表"},{"type":"text","text":"之外，不妨大方地送他一個月會員試試看。在接下來的那一個月，我會負責用內容將他留下來 🙏"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"再次感謝你訂閱、與他人分享區塊勢。"}]}]}

podcast_description: Longer Tables with José Andrés explores all the ways that food shapes our world and makes us who we are. In each episode, José talks to friends from the worlds of culinary and creative arts, politics, and media: Stacey Abrams, Ron Howard, Yo-Yo Ma, Eric Ripert, and Liev Schreiber, and more. He also takes listeners into his home kitchen to learn his favorite recipes, and answers their burning culinary questions.

podcast_description: A Worcester Sucks production, Worcester's Good But Hurts (WGBH) is a weekly recap of the significant happenings in Worcester,  Massachusetts, a city widely regarded as mediocre, frumpish, cartoonish,  down-on-its-luck, gritty, terrible, smelly, trashy, worthless,  insignificant, destitute, inconsolable, irreparable etc. The podcast is  hosted by Worcester Sucks and I Love It author Bill Shaner and Dan Anderson, fellow co-host of Highway 69 and an apprentice at the Worcester-based Ideal Americana Tattoo Company.

podcast_description: What’d You Do This Weekend? is a hilarious podcast with cartoonist Hilary Campbell and writer Derek Boeckelmann who are obviously best friends who are very very funny. Every week they’ll answer that age old question, what did you do this weekend? With tales of New York vs LA, delivery vs. pickup, boys vs. girls, each week Hilary and Derek invite guests to get into every aspect of what it means to be alive from Friday night to Monday morning.

paid_subscription_benefits: ['Subscriber-only posts and full archive', 'Subscriber-only episodes in your podcast app', 'Post comments and join the community']
podcast_description:
True Thirty, with Joey Dumont is a podcast that discusses and debates our society's most politically compelling topics through the lens of slow journalism. Each show is investigated with a focus on narrative as well as discovery. We believe that the complexity of culture cannot be crammed into six-minute television segments, or snippets and memes on social media, where ideology and entertainment is now the priority.

On the program, you’ll hear the opinions of subject matter experts who'll explore the tangled topics of our day. Our collective goal is to help people better understand one another, not win a battle. After listening, you'll be reminded that a proper debate is not about victory, but that of inquiry, education, and viewpoint diversity. So tune in and talk amongst yourselves. You may even learn a thing or two.

hero_text: A weekly dose of sanity and substance amid the spin around climate and sustainability challenges.
name: Sustain What
paid_subscription_benefits: ['Full access to all posts and audio and video content', "Post comments' participate in monthly video chats", 'Help support me hiring a copy editor and/or other support for podcasting and the like']
podcast_description:
Sustain What? is a series of conversations, seeking solutions where complexity and consequence collide on the sustainability frontier. 

This program contains audio highlights from hundreds of video webcasts hosted by Andy Revkin, founder of the Columbia Climate School’s Initiative for Communication and Sustainability. 
Dale Willman is the associate director of the initiative. 

Revkin and Willman believe sustainability has no meaning on its own. The first step toward success is to ask: Sustain what? How? And for whom?

hero_text: Credo quia absurdum
name: Absurdus
paid_subscription_benefits: ['Subscriber-only posts and full archive', 'Post comments and join the community', 'Exclusive short stories']
podcast_description:
I thought to do something different for this week’s post. Instead of writing my thoughts out into a coherent, essay-like article, I wanted to test out my vocal cords. Though I do not yet have the proper equipment to guarantee an optimal listening experience, it does sound significantly better than I thought it would!
As a thank you for everyone who supports my Substack financially, I have limited the accessibility to paying subscribers only.
I hope you enjoy the first episode of the Absurdus Podcast!

name: The Respondent with Greg Ellis
paid_subscription_benefits: ['Subscriber-only posts and full archive', 'Post comments and join the community']
podcast_description:
In 2020 Greg Ellis set out on a journey to explore the condition of the male experience via a new video and podcast series, The Respondent.

The Respondent is a multimedia conversation on positive masculinity; a whodunnit, in which Greg—as both lead detective and key perpetrator—works to track down the co-conspirators of men’s demise and the secrets to their reclamation. It’s also an exploration of how becoming a modern man today demands we reimagine masculinity, rethink fatherhood and revitalize our image of family.

Season one guests include experts, educators, and celebrity Respondents discussing agitating topics including family, philosophy, fatherhood, psychology, politics, family law, pop culture, entertainment, and much more...

paid_subscription_benefits: ['Subscriber-only posts and full archive', 'Post comments, join the community events, exclusive giveaways', 'Early access to LIVING WITH PEOPLE I WANT TO PUNCH IN THE THROAT']
podcast_description: Join New York Times bestselling author of People I Want to Punch in the Throat Jen Mann as she chats up some of the most interesting people she‘s ever met on the interwebs, in elevators, and on the street. Jen hates pants and loves f-bombs. Don‘t bother her with small talk about the weather. She asks the tough questions like, ”Are you wearing pants right now?” and ”What are you even doing with your life right now?” You‘ll laugh, you‘ll cry, you‘ll be enraged, you‘re welcome.
podcast_title: No Pants Required with Jen Mann
